cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CE, cs.CR, cs.DS 

The paper proposes a new formulation for addressing reinforcement learning problems in settings with observational data, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper also introduces a new benchmark for evaluating deconfounding RL algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). Additionally, the paper deals with confounders, which are a common problem in causal inference, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
